text: Mats Kirkebirkeland (born 8 May 1989) is a Norwegian politician for the Conservative Party. He served as a deputy representative to the Parliament of Norway from Oslo during the term 2017-2021. He hails from Bergen. ==References== Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:People from Fusa Category:Politicians from Oslo Category:Deputy members of the Storting Category:Conservative Party (Norway) politicians
